<L>__{interior lab kate's office day}
<A>__{katherine coles, a radiant workaholic, types frenetically into the computer while talking on the phone, trying hard not to sound upset.}
<C>__{kate}
<D>__{who's upset? people fall in love, they have to climb back out.}
<P>__{(she laughs but she is not smiling)}
<D>__{so, what? we'll just be friends now, right?}
<A>__{she stops typing and listens for a while. she runs her hand through her hair.}
<C>__{kate}
<D>__{i see. well i appreciate your honesty.}
<P>__{(using her middle}
<D>__{finger she pushes up}
<P>__{her glasses)}
<D>__{no. i will just think of this as surviving another dating accident. take care or good luck or whatever i'm supposed to...}
<A>__{the line goes dead.}
<C>__{kate}
<D>__{...say... goodbye.}
<A>__{dr. plodder bursts in. kate sees his distress and instantly becomes very centered.}
<C>__{dr. plodder}
<D>__{she's back.}
<C>__{kate}
